metadata.name: Self, Ego #178
metadata.description:
The third and final installment of the Self trilogy.

Ego is defined as: the one of the three divisions of the psyche in psychoanalytic theory that serves as the organized conscious mediator between the person and reality especially by functioning both in the perception of and adaptation to reality.

Please see attached fx(text) article or go to https://ty-vek.art/self-trilogy for more on concept/mechanics/etc. It’s a bit of long read, but worth it.

This is an fx(params) project and you will be able to choose exactly what your iteration will look like. For more details on why this is a params project and how to approach that, check out the article.

—————————

All projects are written in vanilla Javascript, composed as SVG and then rendered to a 2d canvas.

There might be slight differences in rendering from browser to browser. This is expected as they might translate the SVG slightly differently. Let's call Chromium renderings canonical. They also render faster there and we love that.

Press "S" to save a PNG.
Press "V" to save a SVG. (Chromium browsers render these pretty well.)

By default, these will render at 2400 x 3200 pixels. This is at density 1.

To render at a larger resolution you can append “&d=2” to the end of the url. This will double the resolution. You can also use 3 or 4 or whatever your browser can handle. Safari tends to have problems with this, so stick with Chromium based browsers (Chrome, Edge, Brave, etc.)

If you want to render as a square image, so it is optimized for ummm.. your pfp or something, you can append “&sq=t” to the url.

If you want to get rid of grain, just append “&g=n”

—————————

metadata.name: sinuosity #235
metadata.description:
sinuosity is defined as:

- (n.) the ability to curve or bend easily and flexibly.

sinuous is defined as a couple of things:

- (adj.) having many curves and turns.
- (adj.) lithe and supple.

each curve anchors to the center. 

maybe that center is a life. (maybe that center is you.)

maybe that curve is a relationship. (or a job.) (or repressed trauma that needs processing.)

maybe that curve has other curves within. (it probably does.)

sometimes there are many curves at once. (usually this the case.) 

occasionally, there may only be one. (life isn’t always so complicated.) 

whatever curves the moment contains it can help to step away and see how they come together. (this is not always easy.)

[cc0] [p5js] [xoxo] [twitter: @heyjeres]

metadata.name: emit #16
metadata.description:
the things we choose 
to consume 
and seek become 
part of us 
they radiate 
from us tangled 
in loops 
drawn to the center
and held close 
or scattered about 
as chaos 
overwhelms
almost always
regardless of shape 
or intent
we emit what we absorb
for better
we hope

[ 4 : 12000x8000* ]
[ 5 : 15000x10000* ]

* higher resolutions can take a while to render.

metadata.name: vapour trails #105
metadata.description:
“first you look so strong, then you fade away
the sun will blind my eyes, i’ll love you anyway
thirsty for your smile, i watch you for a while
you are a vapour trail in a deep blue sky”

— Andy Bell (Ride) (1991)

this collection tries to capture that feeling of lying in the grass
in a park
staring at the sky
fantasizing about your love (if they even exist)
playing out different paths
while smoke from your cigarette (jazz or otherwise)
trails between you and the faraway of everything
feeling grateful to not have to be anywhere
but here (now)

with luck
they lay next to you
and silently you appreciate each tick of the clock
wasted together
until life again gets in the way
and pulls you back
into the fray

[ live view commands ]
[ M : toggle matte ]
[ S : save current size ]
[ 1 : save 2000x3000 png ]
[ 2 : save 4000x6000 png ]
[ 3 : save 6000x9000* png ]
[ 4 : save 8000x12000* png ]
[ 5 : save 10000x15000* png ]

* higher resolutions can take a while to render.

metadata.name: Seasons of Zurich #6
metadata.description:
Generative collection inspired by the oil paintings of Verena Loewensberg, born in Zurich 1912.
A 110 years later, her graphical art encouraged us to revive the work as our NFT debut.
Colour palettes are taken from the sky of Zurich at different seasons.

metadata.name: Atypical Lands #45
metadata.description:
The starting point of this project was to build something generative, but also connected. Each piece here is part of a world of its own, with several continents, seas, anomalies... Pieces from the same world can be assemble to build a larger map with varying colors, reliefs...
Terrains are build using noises and levelsets.

In its default version, the work is placed on a canvas. It is possible to press "F" to switch between the with or without canvas view. The "x" key allows to save a PNG of the current view. The "W" key allows to create a very high quality version of the piece. The piece is fully responsive.

There are about 60 palettes, the rarest versions being those with a light background (8%), transparent background (2%), and also when the painting is extended on the canvas (5%). 20 different worlds are possible, each with its own size (from 2x2 to 4x4).

Implemented by @Aqw_Zert with p5js

metadata.name: Pixel Tunnel II #212
metadata.description:
This is based on a technique I've used to create textured abstract art by starting with a base design and applying millions of small mutations. Each design has a minimum of 1,500,000 mutations.

This design is built in 2 phases.
Phase 1: Aggressive twisted pixel tunnels create a tangled root system.
Phase 2: Less aggressive straight lines break up the sharp root systems and make the colors blend together.

- Higher themes are more rare (50 max)
- Higher patterns are more rare (15 max)

metadata.name: Platonic Poems #45
metadata.description:
A generative blackout poem written with platonic alphabets. The poem is written by redacting certain parts of a generative paragraph, written in a generative alphabet.

The letters are made by hiding certain edges of platonic solids. Somewhat inspired of Manfred Mohr.

Made using p5js.

Denisovich, Feb 2022

metadata.name: 99 recorridos #83
PALIMPSEST #14
metadata.description:
Tossed around by great currents to a point where they forget their original course, they wander blindly, vanishing into oblivion for others to take their place in this grotesque dance that seems to never end.

Press 'p' to pause/unpause the animation.
Press 'c' to activate/deactivate Bézier curves, it may slow down the animation.
Press 's' to save the current image as a PNG file.

metadata.name: Coupé Décalé #171
metadata.description:
Coupé-Décalé is a type of popular dance music originating in Côte d'Ivoire (Ivory Coast).
The term Coupé-Décalé means cut-shifted in french.
A name that perfectly defines the process used in this generative series.

Artist: Estienne
Dec. 2021 / Jan. 2022

metadata.name: Strata #26
metadata.description:
A generative series inspired by the work of Vera Molnár, Strata explores the diversity that can come from one shape - the simple rectangle.

With 16 properties and ~600 palettes, I hope that each mint offers something unique and special.

Exploration is fully open and will be left open post-mint :)
